  "text": "We previously predicted the existence of U2 via an analysis of coding potential and synonymous site conservation across the two torovirus genomes available at that time [CITATION_1] . Six additional torovirus genome sequences have now become available. We therefore extended the bioinformatics analysis using all eight currently available torovirus genome sequences (Fig. 13) . Since the U2 ORF overlaps ORF1a, leading to constraint on dS, the dN/dS analysis is not appropriate for U2. MLOGD analysis indicated that the U2 ORF has a higher coding potential than the corresponding part of ORF1a (Fig. 13) . Overlapping genes are thought mainly to evolve through \"overprinting\" of an 1 ϩ x) scale. Negative-sense reads (gray) are displayed below the x axis. A ϩ12-nt offset has been applied to read 5=-end positions to map approximate P-site positions.",
